
[1]fervently

   FERV'ENTLY, adv.

   1. Earnestly; eagerly; vehemently; with great warmth.

   2. With pious ardor; with earnest zeal; ardently.

   Epaphras - saluteth you, laboring fervently for you in prayers. Col. 4.
